|     This course includes 8 fundamental chapters in Python_programming and I think this is really importance in case that    |
|  you go on the DataFrame; Data Analyst; Computer Vision, Image Processing, Signal Processing, etc.                          |
|      Below is the detail of each chapters                                                                                   |
|*****************************************************************************************************************************|
|                                             CHAPTER 1. VARIABLES & DATA TYPES.                                              |
|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|    In this chapter, we will discuss the variables, naming variables and how to distinguish the various of datatypes in      |
|  Python; such as: numeric, list, bool, date-time, ....                                                                      |
|     Moreover, understanding the operations of string, numeric (int, float, binary, ...) is nescessary to study the other    |
|  topics; e.g., data analyst, computer vision, natural language processing, and so on.                                       |
|*****************************************************************************************************************************|
|                                              CHAPTER 2. CONDITIONALS, LOOPING.                                              |
|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|    In this chapter, we will study the definition of conditions, also how to make a loop, using for, while, and if, cases.   |
|    Obviously, we will have a lots of exciting examples to illustrations! Don't be worried about this!                       |
|*****************************************************************************************************************************|
|                                         CHAPTER 3. FUNCTIONS & FUNCTION_ARGUMENTS.                                          |
|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|    Understanding the function, writing the function and optimal your computation is a very useful technique to become a     |
|  good programmers, also to deal with the complexity problems in the real life.                                              |
|*****************************************************************************************************************************|
|                                             CHAPTER 4. ERRORS & EXCEPTIONS                                                  |
|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|    An error detected during execution of some Python code is called an exception. So what are they? and how many types of   |
|  them? Go ahead and don't hesitage anymore.                                                                                 |
|*****************************************************************************************************************************|
|                                        CHAPTER 5. CLASSES, OBJECTS & LAMBDA FUNCTIONS                                       |
|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|    In the 3rd chapter, we had undertood the function; so what is lambda function and why we called it be the anomyous func? |
|    Section classes is beyond the scope of this document to provide a complete introduction to object oriented programming.  |
|    In the section of class, we simply introduce the basic to define classes and create custom objects in Python.            |
|*****************************************************************************************************************************|
|                                             CHAPTER 6. MODULES & PACKAGES.                                                  |
|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|    Understanding modules and packages is the first step to reach "Package Development"? A module is nothing else than a     |
| Python file and the file name is the module name with suffix.py appended; so you must take care the folder modules_and_pack |
| in my github!                                                                                                               |
|*****************************************************************************************************************************|
|                                           CHAPTER 7. GRAPHICS WITH MATPLOTLIB                                               |
|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|    This is a nescessary for whom concerns Geomertrics, Computer vision, Data visualization, etc with only matplotlib.       |
|*****************************************************************************************************************************|
|                                       CHAPTER 8. WELCOME TO NUMPY, PANDAS, SEABORN, etc.                                    |
|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|    In the final chapter, I will introduce some popular libraries that may we works daily in Python. The details and its     |
|  applications will be discuss on the other courses. Now, finish this chapter and welcome to Python!                         |
